Instructions
To develop the Flatdango application, please follow the instructions provided below:

Plan out the user interface and how the information will be displayed on the webpage.
Design a database schema that will store the relevant information about the movies, showtimes, and ticket sales.
Build out the backend of the application using a web framework of your choice.
Develop the frontend of the application using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
Test the application and debug any issues.
Deploy the application to a hosting service of your choice.
Technologies Used
The following technologies were used to develop the Flatdango application:

Backend Framework: Flask
Frontend Languages: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
Database: SQLite
Hosting Service: Heroku
Setup
To set up the Flatdango application on your local machine, please follow the instructions provided below:

Clone the repository to your local machine using the following command:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your-username/flatdango.git
Navigate to the project directory:
bash
Copy code
cd flatdango
Install the required dependencies:
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt
Start the Flask server:
arduino
Copy code
flask run
Open your web browser and navigate to http://localhost:5000.
Features
The following features are currently available in the Flatdango application:

Browse movies
View movie details (description, rating, duration)
Select showtime
Purchase tickets
View ticket confirmation
Future Improvements
Here are some potential improvements that could be made to the Flatdango application in the future:

Add user authentication
Allow users to save their favorite movies
Provide recommended movies based on user preferences
Allow users to rate movies and leave reviews